}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority"}],"available_translations":[{"title":"Michelle Heath joins NDA Board as a Non-Executive Director","public_updated_at":"2019-09-27T10:59:58Z","document_type":"news_story","schema_name":"news_article","base_path":"/government/news/michelle-heath-joins-nda-board-as-a-non-executive-director","api_path":"/api/content/government/news/michelle-heath-joins-nda-board-as-a-non-executive-director","withdrawn":false,"content_id":"67c326a9-fa58-48b9-ad1d-d1df784f53e5","locale":"en","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/news/michelle-heath-joins-nda-board-as-a-non-executive-director","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/michelle-heath-joins-nda-board-as-a-non-executive-director","links":{}}]},"description":"The Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (NDA) has today announced the appointment of Michelle Heath to its Board as an additional non-executive director for a 3-year term from 1 October.","details":{"body":"<p>This appointment has been approved by Andrea Leadsom, the Secretary of State for the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy.</p>\n\n<p>Tom Smith, the Chair of the NDA, said:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p class=\"last-child\">I am delighted that Michelle is joining us in support of our vital work decommissioning 17 complex nuclear sites across Wales, Scotland and England.  She has a wealth of relevant and current experience in the nuclear industry which will be a great addition to the Board’s capability.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Michelle Heath has a 20-year track record in the nuclear industry having previously worked for BNFL, Springfields Fuels and Westinghouse Toshiba. </p>\n\n<p>She has wide experience in the UK and internationally, with a strong focus on waste management, treatment and storage. At Westinghouse, Michelle was the Global Product Manager for residues treatment and prior to that she held a number of senior roles at the Springfields nuclear fuel fabrication plant in Lancashire. Michelle holds an MBA and BSc from Lancaster University.</p>\n","image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d8dd11140f0b65e5dbe04c0/michelle-heath960x640.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5d8dd111ed915d556efe16dc/michelle-heath960x640.jpg","alt_text":"Michelle Heath","caption":"Michelle Heath","credit":""},"change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-09-27T09:08:11.286Z"}]},"document_status":"published","created_by":"Melissa Arnot Reid","last_updated_by":"Lucy Walker","political":false,"government":{"title":"2015 Conservative government","slug":"2015-conservative-government","start_date":"2015-05-07T23:00:00.000Z","end_date":"","current":true},"document_schema":"news"}